  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6601.52 sitting just below the max positive gamma wall at 6605 and the GEX flip at 6617, dealers are currently in moderate selling mode to hedge their long gamma positions. The massive positive GEX concentration between 6600-6620 (52+ billion) creates a strong gravitational pull that should cap upside momentum and provide support on any dips. Key levels to watch: 6590 negative gamma floor where dealer buying accelerates, 6605 resistance where selling intensifies, and 6617 flip point where regime dynamics shift.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to get stuck in the 6590-6620 range with dealers smoothing out moves.",
